    <thetext>As discussed during the Apr 9 meeting, specifying `RegExp.prototype.toString` completely is a can of worms, and we should leave it up to implementations.

Waldemar suggested the spec should add a requirement that makes `eval(RegExp(string))` hold true for all values of string (browsers get this wrong).</thetext>
  </long_desc><long_desc isprivate="0" >
